//! Reject: non-BitCopy match destructure on a TEMPORARY (fresh-value)
//! scrutinee with a binding arm (partial extraction).
//!
//! `match make() { Pair { a: x, b: _ } => x }` extracts `a` into a binding and
//! wildcards `b`. The scrutinee is a temporary returned by a call, so it has no
//! composite drop. The bound field `x` is loaded via `RecordFieldLoad`, which
//! seeds it as a projection-alias of the parent; without a consume mark on the
//! parent (a temporary cannot be consume-marked — there is no binding to mark),
//! `derive_cow_sole_owner` excludes `x` from the drop allow-set and its payload
//! leaks. The wildcarded `b` is inline-dropped, so the net leak is the
//! extracted-but-aliased binder, one allocation per evaluation.
//!
//! The scrutinee-shape gate refuses this fail-closed with
//! `E_NOT_YET_IMPLEMENTED: MIR lowering for non-BitCopy match destructure on
//! temporary scrutinee`. Binding the scrutinee to a local first
//! (`let scrutinee = make(); match scrutinee { … }`) routes through the
//! consume-mark + binder-untaint path that drops every field exactly once.
//!
//! Observable contract: `hew check` fails non-zero with the temporary-scrutinee
//! diagnostic. A regression that admitted temporary scrutinees would let this
//! file `check` green and leak the extracted binder on every evaluation.

type Pair {
    a: string,
    b: string,
}

fn make() -> Pair {
    Pair {
        a: string_concat("a-", "payload"),
        b: string_concat("b-", "payload"),
    }
}

fn main() -> i64 {
    let _s = match make() {
        Pair { a: x, b: _ } => x,
    };
    0
}
